'''St. Martinus University Faculty of Medicine''' ('''SMUFOM''') is a [[private university]] located in [[Willemstad]], [[Curaçao]], in the [[Caribbean]]. St. Martinus confers upon its graduates the [[Doctor of Medicine]] (MD) degree.

==History==

Originally St. Martinus College,<ref>{{cite journal |last1=FM Beureu |year=2012|month=8|volume=1|issue =2|title=Become a healer at the Island of Healing|journal=Future Medicine|pages=30-31|publisher=[[D. C. Books]] |url= http://issuu.com/dcmedia/docs/fm_ii_issue_pdf_for_web/31|accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref> a Catholic girls' school, the university was transformed into its current role as a medical school by a John Daryanani-led group at the request of the local Roman Catholic Church, and established as St. Martinus University on May 22, 2000.<ref name="REG">{{cite web|url=http://www2.curacao-chamber.an/info/registry/excerpt.asp?mode=edit&companyid=84720&establishmentnr=0&legalformid=51 |title=Security Check |publisher=.curacao-chamber.an |date= |accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref> In October 2005, Daryanani said the school had half the number of students it needed to break even,<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Ceaser|first1=Mike|year=2005|month=10|volume=52|issue=10 |title=Sun, Sand, and an M.D.(Caribbean medical schools)|journal=[[The Chronicle of Higher Education]]|pages=A55–A60|publisher=The Chronicle of Higher Education Inc. |url= http://business.highbeam.com/434953/article-1G1-147067654/sun-sand-and-md|accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref> and in October 2007, Banco de Caribe announced an auction of the university property.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.liveincuracao.com/index.php?p=436 |title=The Curaçao Islandguide - Yet the end for St. Martinus University |publisher=Liveincuracao.com |date= |accessdate=2013-02-26}}</ref> Daryanani began seeking a new buyer for the school and in early 2008, Henry Chau, the chairman and CEO of the Maple Leaf Investment Fund, was appointed as new chairman of the university. Chau left in April 2009, citing differences with Daryanani, and the university briefly closed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pearlfmradio.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=2040&Itemid=73 |title=Medical students claim their rights |publisher=Pearl FM Radio |date= |accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref> In 2010,{{cn|date=March 2013}} SMU reopened under the administration of Priyamvada Sharma, who currently serves as the university's managing director.<ref name="REG" />

==Curriculum==

The MD program at St. Martinus University consists of four 20-week semesters of [[Medicine#Basic sciences|basic sciences]] that are completed at the university's Curacao campus, and 80 weeks of [[clerkship (medicine)|clinical clerkships]] that are completed at affiliated hospitals in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.martinus.edu/md-program/ |title=M.D. Program &#124; St. Martinus University |publisher=Martinus.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.martinus.edu/clinical-clerkships/ |title=Clinical Clerkships &#124; St. Martinus University |publisher=Martinus.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref>

St. Martinus also offers a one year [[pre-medical]] program for high school graduates who have not completed the necessary prerequisites for the MD program.<ref>http://www.martinus.edu/pre-medical/</ref>

==Accreditation==

St. Martinus University was chartered by the Government of the Netherlands Antilles in 2001 and recognized by the Curacao Ministry of Health in 2005.<ref>http://india.martinus.edu/Documents/Accreditation/2001%2010%2016%20Charter%20SMU.pdf</ref><ref>http://india.martinus.edu/Documents/Accreditation/2005%2009%2013%20BC%20to%20SMU%20recognition%20letter.pdf</ref> St. Martinus University is listed in the FAIMER [[International Medical Education Directory]] (IMED) and in the [[WHO Directory of Medical Schools|AVICENNA Directory for medicine]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://avicenna.ku.dk/database/medicine/ |title=AVICENNA Directory Medicine – University of Copenhagen |publisher=Avicenna.ku.dk |date= |accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref><ref>https://imed.faimer.org/results.asp?country=667&school=st%2E+martinus+university+faculty+of+medicine&currpage=1&cname=CURACAO&city=&region=CA&rname=Central+America%2FCaribbean&psize=25</ref>

St. Martinus University is recognized as a designated educational institution by the Canada Student Loans Program (CSLP).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tools.canlearn.ca/cslgs-scpse/cln-cln/50/reea-mdl/reea-mdl-1-eng.do?nom-name=inter |title=List of Designated Educational Institutions - CanLearn.ca |publisher=Tools.canlearn.ca |date= |accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref>

===Licensure restrictions===
On April 16, 2013, the [[Medical Council of India]] listed St. Martinus University Faculty of Medicine as an institution whose graduates are ineligible for the [[Medical Council of India Screening Test]].<ref name="MCI">{{cite web|url=http://www.mciindia.org/tools/announcement/PUBLIC_NOTICE_ELIGIBILITY_16_04_2013.pdf |title=Public Notice regarding Eligibility Certificate |publisher=www.mciindia.org|date= |accessdate=2013-05-02}}</ref>

